fields.name: Enabled
fields.description: false if the Azure Active Directory provider should not be enabled despite the set registration; otherwise, true.

fields.name: IsAutoProvisioned
fields.description:
Gets a value indicating whether the Azure AD configuration was auto-provisioned using 1st party tooling.
This is an internal flag primarily intended to support the Azure Management Portal. Users should not
read or write to this property.

fields.name: Login
fields.description: The configuration settings of the Azure Active Directory login flow.

fields.name: Registration
fields.description: The configuration settings of the Azure Active Directory app registration.

fields.name: Validation
fields.description: The configuration settings of the Azure Active Directory token validation flow.
